PINNACLE Club Program – Detailed Explanation


---

1️⃣ Program Overview

This program manages a club member list using a singly linked list.

Each member has a PRN number and name.

We can add general members, president, secretary, count total members, and display the member list.


Key Concepts:

Singly Linked List → Each node points to the next.

Head pointer → points to the first member.

Tail pointer → points to the last member.

Dynamic memory allocation → new nodes are created at runtime using new.



---

2️⃣ Include Libraries

#include<iostream>
#include<string>
using namespace std;

#include<iostream> → for input/output (cin, cout).

#include<string> → to use string datatype for names.

using namespace std; → avoids std:: prefix.



---

3️⃣ Node Structure

struct node {
    int prn;
    string name;
    node* next;
};

Explanation:

prn → stores the unique PRN number of a member.

name → stores member's name.

next → pointer to the next node in the linked list.


Example:

Member: PRN=101, Name=Rudrani → Node contains these values and points to next member.



---

4️⃣ Pinclub Class

class pinclub {
public:
    node *head,*tail,*nnode;
    pinclub() { head=tail=NULL; }

    void create();           // Add members
    void insertion();        // Add president
    void insertionlast();    // Add secretary
    void count();            // Count members
    void display();          // Display members
};

Explanation:

head → first member.

tail → last member.

nnode → temporary node used for adding new members.

Constructor initializes head and tail as NULL (list empty initially).

Functions for creating list, inserting at start/end, counting, and displaying.



---

5️⃣ Create Members

void pinclub::create() {
    char m;
    do {
        nnode=new node;
        nnode->next=NULL;
        cout<<endl<<"Enter prn number: ";
        cin>>nnode->prn;
        cout<<endl<<"Enter name of user: ";
        cin>>nnode->name;
        if(head==NULL) head=tail=nnode;
        else { tail->next=nnode; tail=nnode; }
        cout<<endl<<"Do you want to continue(y or n): ";
        cin>>m;
    } while(m=='y');
    display();
}

Explanation:

1. Creates members dynamically using new node.


2. nnode->next=NULL → last node points to NULL.


3. Takes PRN and Name input.


4. If head is NULL, this is first member, so head & tail point to nnode.


5. Else, add to end using tail->next=nnode; tail=nnode.


6. Loops until user enters 'n'.


7. Calls display() to show current members.



Example Run:

Enter prn number: 101
Enter name of user: Rudrani
Do you want to continue(y or n): y
Enter prn number: 102
Enter name of user: Anushka
Do you want to continue(y or n): n

Linked List Now:

head -> [101, Rudrani] -> [102, Anushka] -> NULL
tail -> points to [102, Anushka]


---

6️⃣ Insert President

void pinclub::insertion() {
    nnode=new node;
    nnode->next=NULL;
    cout<<endl<<"Enter president name: ";
    cin>>nnode->name;
    cout<<endl<<"Enter prn of president: ";
    cin>>nnode->prn;
    nnode->next=head;
    head=nnode;
    display();
}

Explanation:

Creates new node for president.

Inserts at beginning of linked list (nnode->next=head; head=nnode).

President is always first in list.


Example:

Before: [101, Rudrani] -> [102, Anushka]

Add President PRN=100, Name=Shraddha →


head -> [100, Shraddha] -> [101, Rudrani] -> [102, Anushka] -> NULL


---

7️⃣ Insert Secretary

void pinclub::insertionlast() {
    nnode=new node;
    nnode->next=NULL;
    cout<<endl<<"Enter name of secretary : ";
    cin>>nnode->name;
    cout<<endl<<"Enter prn of secretary: ";
    cin>>nnode->prn;
    tail->next=nnode;
    tail=nnode;
    display();
}

Explanation:

Creates new node for secretary.

Inserts at end of list.

Updates tail to new node.


Example:

Before: [100, Shraddha] -> [101, Rudrani] -> [102, Anushka]

Add Secretary PRN=103, Name=Isha →


[100, Shraddha] -> [101, Rudrani] -> [102, Anushka] -> [103, Isha] -> NULL
tail -> points to [103, Isha]


---

8️⃣ Count Members

void pinclub::count() {
    int c=0;
    temp=head;
    while(temp!=NULL) { c++; temp=temp->next; }
    cout<<"\nTotal members in club are: "<<c<<endl;
}

Explanation:

Start from head, traverse list until NULL, count each node.

Prints total number of members.


Example:

Current list: [100, Shraddha] -> [101, Rudrani] -> [102, Anushka] -> [103, Isha]

Output: Total members in club are: 4



---

9️⃣ Display Members

void pinclub::display() {
    cout<<endl<<"YOUR UPDATED CLUB DATA IS: "<<endl;
    if(head==NULL) cout<<endl<<"Club is empty";
    else {
        cout<<"\nPRN NO.\t NAME"<<endl;
        temp=head;
        while(temp!=NULL) {
            cout<<endl<<temp->prn<<"    "<<temp->name;
            temp=temp->next;
        }
    }
}

Explanation:

Prints all members from head to tail.

Traverses linked list using temp.

Displays PRN and Name in tabular format.


Example Output:

YOUR UPDATED CLUB DATA IS: 

PRN NO.   NAME
100       Shraddha
101       Rudrani
102       Anushka
103       Isha


---

10️⃣ Main Function

int main() {
    pinclub l1;
    int choice;
    cout<<"\nWelcome to PINNACLE Club"<<endl;
    l1.create();

    do {
        cout<<"\n1. Insert President";
        cout<<"\n2. Insert Secretary";
        cout<<"\n3. Count Members";
        cout<<"\n4. Display Members";
        cout<<"\n5. Exit";
        cout<<"\nEnter your choice: ";
        cin>>choice;
        switch(choice) {
            case 1: l1.insertion(); break;
            case 2: l1.insertionlast(); break;
            case 3: l1.count(); break;
            case 4: l1.display(); break;
            case 5: cout<<"\nExiting..."; break;
            default: cout<<"\nInvalid choice!";
        }
    } while(choice!=5);

    return 0;
}

Explanation:

Creates PINNACLE club object l1.

Calls create() → to add initial members.

Menu-driven program:

1. Insert President → at beginning


2. Insert Secretary → at end


3. Count Members


4. Display Members


5. Exit program




Example Run:

Welcome to PINNACLE Club
Enter prn number: 101
Enter name of user: Rudrani
Do you want to continue(y or n): y
Enter prn number: 102
Enter name of user: Anushka
Do you want to continue(y or n): n

Menu:
1. Insert President
2. Insert Secretary
3. Count Members
4. Display Members
5. Exit
Enter your choice: 1

Enter president name: Shraddha
Enter prn of president: 100

List updated with president at head.



