11️⃣ Viva Questions and Answers

1. What is a linked list?

A dynamic data structure where each element (node) points to the next.



2. Why use head and tail?

head → first node

tail → last node (to quickly add at end)



3. Difference between inserting at start and end?

Start → new node points to head, head updated.

End → tail’s next points to new node, tail updated.



4. Why do we use dynamic memory (new) instead of array?

Number of members is unknown at compile-time.

Dynamic memory allows flexible size.



5. What will happen if list is empty and we display?

Program prints “Club is empty”.



6. Why do we traverse using temp?

To avoid losing head pointer while moving through the list.



7. Can we insert president and secretary without creating members?

Yes, the list can be empty; insertion will make them first/last node.





